profile_positions.description:
Role: 
Responsible for processing data into information, information into insight, and insight into business decisions.

Responsibilities:
1. Transforms data into information used for decision-making.
    - Collect and prepare data;
    - Use data analysis and data visualisation to answer business questions in the most effective way;
    - (Support to) Maintain and drive key reports, metrics, and workflows;
    - Adopt and propose new approaches in data analytics.

2. Shares data & analytics and collaborate with internal stakeholders.
    - Support the technical development of other team members on data & analytics;
    - Communicate effectively, collaboratively, and changes constructively;
    - Actively participate in business and/or analytics team activities and suggest ways of achieving objectives (stand-up, planing meetings, retrospectives);
    - Provide and receive feedback from peers and direct stakeholders.

3. Maintains an understanding of current data analytics practices.
    - Networks and proactively connects with craft peers beyond the team scope;
    - Participate in training, conferences & workshops.
